content: I think the worm's character would probably have a lot of self-doubt and anxiety when it comes to approaching Sarah. He may be charming in one sense, but unattractive and off putting in his lack of confidence and self-effacing nature. Even when giving good advice, he hesitates, and his own doubt can plant seeds of doubt in Sarah that grow, as the cracks in his character and integrity begin to propagate in response to stressors from the introduction of Jareth into the dynamic.
